# Notion

Call the Notion REST API as the connected user via the bundled helper.

{{ACTION_AVAILABILITY_SECTION}}

## Usage

    python .opencode/skills/notion/notion_api.py <command> [args]

Read commands auto-paginate and prune empty fields. The writes are
`create-page`, `append`, `comment`, `update-page`, `update-block`, and
`delete-block`. Use `--raw` to skip empty-field pruning;
`python notion_api.py <command> -h` shows its flags.

### The connected user

```
python notion_api.py me
```

### Users

```
python notion_api.py users [--limit N]
```

### Search pages and data sources

```
python notion_api.py search "roadmap" [--filter page|data_source] [--limit N]
```

The query is optional — omit it to list everything the integration can access.

### Read a page

```
python notion_api.py page PAGE_ID
```

### Read a page/block's child blocks (its content)

```
python notion_api.py blocks BLOCK_ID [--limit N]
```

### List a database's data sources

```
python notion_api.py database DATABASE_ID
```

A database contains one or more data sources; this returns each with its `id`
and `name`. Use a data source id with `data-source` and `query` below.

### Read a data source's schema

```
python notion_api.py data-source DATA_SOURCE_ID
```

### Query a data source's rows

```
python notion_api.py query DATA_SOURCE_ID [--limit N]
```

### Create a page (write)

```
python notion_api.py create-page (--parent-page PAGE_ID | --parent-data-source DATA_SOURCE_ID) \
  --title "Title" [--text "First paragraph"]
```

### Append content to a page/block (write)

```
python notion_api.py append BLOCK_ID --text "A new paragraph"
```

### Comment on a page (write)

```
python notion_api.py comment PAGE_ID "Looking into this"
```

### Update a page's title/icon, or archive it (write)

```
python notion_api.py update-page PAGE_ID [--title "New title"] [--icon 📌] [--archive | --restore]
```

At least one of `--title`, `--icon`, `--archive`, or `--restore` is required.
`--archive` moves the page to trash; `--restore` brings it back.

### Update or archive a block (write)

```
python notion_api.py update-block BLOCK_ID [--text "Replacement text"] [--archive | --restore]
```

`--text` replaces a paragraph block's content (the block must be a paragraph).
At least one of `--text`, `--archive`, or `--restore` is required.

### Delete a block (write)

```
python notion_api.py delete-block BLOCK_ID
```

Moves the block to trash. To archive/restore a whole page use `update-page`.

## Output

JSON on stdout. List commands return `{"ok": true, "<key>": [...], "count": N,
"truncated": bool}` (`truncated` means more results existed past `--limit`).
Failures return `{"ok": false, "status": <code>, "error": "<message>"}` and exit
non-zero — surface the error rather than retrying blindly.

## Notes

- IDs are Notion object ids (UUIDs), with or without dashes. Get them from
  `search`, `blocks`, `database`, or `query` output.
- The connected user's token is injected by the egress gateway — send no
  credentials yourself.
- The integration's capabilities (read / write / comment) are set by the admin
  on the Notion integration. A 401 / 403 usually means the integration lacks the
  needed capability or hasn't been shared with the page — tell the user rather
  than retrying.
